      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LADY MOSCATO (1) is the interesting runner on resumption. She's a very well-bred filly who was last seen tackling the G1 Blue Diamond, acquitting herself well in ninth. She's had three trials in Sydney leading in and draws well, expect she's very hard to catch. ONE DAY AT A TIME (2) ran first up in the 2yo sprint final at Flemington and ran well there behind the handy Stars Of Dom. She'd shown good ability last time in and should be better suited coming back to 1000m second up. EGYPTIAN DANCER (4) has been right there in two runs back having chased home two smart ones last time at Caulfield, into a tough headwind that day. Has race fitness and will take catching. FONTALICIOUS (3) is coming along nicely and should be right there again.",
